Que 1. What is the Lambda expression in Java? How is it used in Java 8?
Ans: The Lambda expression in Java represents the instances of functional interfaces. It is a short anonymous function in Java.
	It is introduced in Java to make code more concise and readable, especially when working in collections and streams.
	Syntax: (parameters) -> {expression} or (parameters) -> {statement}
		e.g., (a , b) -> (a + b);

