Que 2. Explain the concept of Function interface?
Ans: In java a function interface has only one abstract method, but it can have multiple default and static methods but only one abstract method.
  It is designed specifically to work with Lambda expressions in java 8.
  It has built-in annotation to ensure it is a functional interface with one abstract method.
   An abstract method in a functional interface is without a body that must be implemented by the subclass of the interface or implemented by the class using overriding.
   
   e.g.
		@FunctionalInterface
		interface MyInterface{
			void sayHello();
		}
		
	Java provides the built-in functional interfaces that are below:
	1. Function,
	2. Predicate,
	3. Consumer,
	4. Supplier
	
