Que 4. What is method references, and how are they different from lambda expressions?
Ans: Method References: It allows the method or constructors directly by their names using the '::' (double colon) operators.
	These are some method references mentioned below:
	1. Static method References (ClassName::staticMethod),
	2. Instance method Reference (ObjectName:: instanceMethod or ClassName:: instanceMethod)
	3. Constructor references (ClassName :: new)
	
	Method references is different from lambda expressions.
	It does not define the new function; it refers to the existing method.
	It is used when the method already exists. But lambda is used when we need custom logic.
	It is more readable, but Lambda is more flexible.
	
