Que 6: Explain the use of the reduce() method in Streams.
Ans: Reduce method used to reduce the element of a stream to single stream.
	 It is like folding operation it takes a sequence of values and repeatedly applies a combining function until only one value remains.
	 The method typically takes two parameters:
	 1. Identity: the initial value for the operation.
	 2. Accumulator: A function that takes two parameters and returns a new result.
	 
	 Reduce method has three variants of reduce().
	 1. reduce(accumulator) - when you don't have an identity and the stream might be empty.
	  	return type - Optional<T>
	  	
	  	Optional<Integer> max = numbers.stream()
	  									.reduce(Integer::max);
	  	
	  	
	  2. reduce(identity, accumulator) - It takes the identity as initial value and binaryoperator and applies the accumulator repeatedly to combine the element.
	  	e.g.Summming the numbers starting from 0.
	  	
	  		List<Intger> numbers = Arrays.asList(1,2,3,4);
	  		int sum = numbers.stream()
	  						 .reduce(0, (a,b) -> a+b);
	  	
	  3. reduce(identity, accumulator, combiner) - used in parallel streams to merge result from different threads.
	  		List<String> words = Arrays.asList("Java", "is", "cool");
	  		String s = words.stream()
	  						.reduce("", (a, b) -> a + " " + b );
	  


