Que 7. What is the purpose of Collectors.groupingBy()?
Ans: Grouping is powerful features provided by the Collectors class, specifically through the Collectors.groupingBy() method.
	 It allows the group of a stream based on the classification function.
	 It is equivalent of the SQL GROUP BY clause.
	 It takes a stream of objects and organizes them into a Map<K, List<T>>
	  where K = key (result of the grouping function)
	  		T = elements from stream
	  		
	  Collectors.groupBy() is used to group stream elements into a map based on a key function, making easier to analyze and organize.
	  
	  e.g. Map<String, List<Employee>> groupbyDept = employee.stream()
	  														 .collect(Collectors.groupBy(Employee::getDepartment));
	  	   key - department name
	  	   value - list of employees in that dept.


