Que 9. Why is Stream API considered lazy in execution?
Ans: The Java stream API is considered lazy in execution because it does not process data immediately when operations are called.
	 Execution starts only with terminal operations.
	 Elements are processed one by one(not all at once)
	 When we create a stream and apply operations like:
	 	filer()
	 	map()
	 	sorted()
	 No actual computation happens at that moment,
	 instead these operations are stored as pipeline of instructions, executed only when a terminal operation is called.
	 
